==English==

===Etymology===
From James Alfred [[Van Allen]], US [[physicist]].

===Noun===
'''[[van|Van]] [[Allen]] [[belt]]''' 

# Either of two [[torus]]-shaped areas of high-energy [[charge]]d [[particle]]s which partly [[surround]] [[Earth]], trapped by its [[magnetic field]]. The areas are characterised by intense [[radiation]]. When the belts "overload", particles strike the upper atmosphere and [[fluoresce]], causing the [[polar]] [[aurora]].
# Any of similar areas around another [[planet]].

====Synonyms====
*[[Van Allen radiation belt]]

